---
---

  <section class="section appear" id="prompts">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="no">08</span>
      <h2>Prompts you can name, version, and ship.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="section-intro">
      <p class="lede">
        <span class="hot">jig prompt get comprehensive-review-loop --var base=main</span> resolves a named prompt across three namespaces, renders the body through MiniJinja, and prints the result to stdout — nothing else, even with global <span class="mono">--json</span>.
      </p>
      <p class="sub">
        Prompts are <b>Markdown with YAML frontmatter</b> on disk. <span class="mono hot">user:</span> prompts live in your Jig config dir, <span class="mono hot">repo:</span> prompts live in <span class="mono">.jig/prompts/</span> beside the contract, and read-only <span class="mono hot">pack:</span> prompts ship as installable prompt-packs. Override the storage root with <span class="mono">JIG_PROMPT_HOME</span>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 3 namespaces · same chrome as the vault zones -->
    <div class="brokered">
      <div class="brokered-zone z-vault">
        <div class="stamp"><span class="stamp-n">01</span> user:</div>
        <div class="zone-body">
          <div class="zone-row"><span>path</span><b>~/.config/jig/prompts/user/</b></div>
          <div class="zone-row"><span>scope</span><b>writable · across repos</b></div>
          <div class="zone-row"><span>format</span><b>name.md · YAML frontmatter</b></div>
          <div class="zone-row"><span>default</span><b>unqualified writes land here</b></div>
        </div>
        <div class="zone-divider">contents · names only</div>
        <div class="zone-list">
          <div><span class="zone-key">comprehensive-review-loop</span><span class="zone-bar"></span></div>
          <div><span class="zone-key">commit-message-rewrite</span><span class="zone-bar"></span></div>
          <div><span class="zone-key">spec-from-thread</span><span class="zone-bar"></span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="brokered-sep" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 40 20" width="40" height="20">
          <line x1="2"  y1="10" x2="38" y2="10" stroke="#ff4d1f" stroke-width="1"/>
          <path d="M 32 5 L 38 10 L 32 15" stroke="#ff4d1f" stroke-width="1" fill="none"/>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <div class="brokered-zone z-broker">
        <div class="stamp"><span class="stamp-n">02</span> repo:</div>
        <div class="zone-body">
          <div class="zone-row"><span>path</span><b>&lt;repo&gt;/.jig/prompts/</b></div>
          <div class="zone-row"><span>scope</span><b>writable · checked in</b></div>
          <div class="zone-row"><span>use for</span><b>team-shared prompts</b></div>
          <div class="zone-row"><span>resolves</span><b>before user: on tie</b></div>
        </div>
        <div class="zone-divider">contents · names only</div>
        <div class="zone-list">
          <div><span class="zone-key">release-checklist</span><span class="zone-bar"></span></div>
          <div><span class="zone-key">pr-review-this-repo</span><span class="zone-bar"></span></div>
          <div><span class="zone-key">migration-policy-check</span><span class="zone-bar"></span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="brokered-sep" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 40 20" width="40" height="20">
          <line x1="2"  y1="10" x2="38" y2="10" stroke="#ff4d1f" stroke-width="1"/>
          <path d="M 32 5 L 38 10 L 32 15" stroke="#ff4d1f" stroke-width="1" fill="none"/>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <div class="brokered-zone z-trace">
        <div class="stamp"><span class="stamp-n">03</span> pack:</div>
        <div class="zone-body">
          <div class="zone-row"><span>path</span><b>~/.config/jig/prompt-packs/&lt;pack&gt;/</b></div>
          <div class="zone-row"><span>scope</span><b>read-only · vendored</b></div>
          <div class="zone-row"><span>install</span><b>jig prompt import pack.json</b></div>
          <div class="zone-row"><span>schema</span><b>versioned JSON archive · v1</b></div>
        </div>
        <div class="zone-divider">unqualified reads must be unambiguous</div>
        <div class="zone-allow"><span class="mono hot">user:</span> · <span class="mono hot">repo:</span> · <span class="mono hot">pack:&lt;name&gt;:&lt;prompt&gt;</span> resolves the conflict</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- features + listing panel -->
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature-list">
        <div class="feature-row"><span class="feature-num">01</span><div><b>Three namespaces, one resolver.</b> <span class="mono hot">user:</span>, <span class="mono hot">repo:</span>, and <span class="mono hot">pack:&lt;pack&gt;:</span> share a name table. Unqualified reads must resolve to exactly one prompt — collisions error with a list, not a silent winner.</div></div>
        <div class="feature-row"><span class="feature-num">02</span><div><b>MiniJinja templating built in.</b> Bodies render with <span class="mono hot">--var KEY=VALUE</span> (repeatable). Use <span class="mono">--raw</span> to print the stored body unchanged when the prompt is its own escape hatch.</div></div>
        <div class="feature-row"><span class="feature-num">03</span><div><b>Authoring is a text file.</b> <span class="mono hot">jig prompt add</span> writes Markdown with YAML frontmatter; <span class="mono hot">jig prompt edit</span> opens it in <span class="mono">$EDITOR</span> / <span class="mono">$VISUAL</span> (arguments like <span class="mono">code -w</span> are honored). Re-adding preserves description and tags unless you override them.</div></div>
        <div class="feature-row"><span class="feature-num">04</span><div><b>Find what you've named.</b> <span class="mono hot">jig prompt list</span> shows names, descriptions, tags, and source. <span class="mono hot">jig prompt search</span> matches names, descriptions, and tags by default; pass <span class="mono">--body</span> to grep the prompt bodies too.</div></div>
        <div class="feature-row"><span class="feature-num">05</span><div><b>Copy straight to the agent.</b> <span class="mono hot">jig prompt copy</span> renders and pipes to the system clipboard — <span class="mono">pbcopy</span>, <span class="mono">wl-copy</span>, <span class="mono">xclip</span>, or the override in <span class="mono">JIG_PROMPT_CLIPBOARD_COMMAND</span>.</div></div>
        <div class="feature-row"><span class="feature-num">06</span><div><b>Portable as a JSON archive.</b> <span class="mono hot">jig prompt export</span> emits a versioned bundle of prompts and packs; <span class="mono hot">jig prompt import</span> replaces existing entries and reports which were overwritten. Same on-disk schema across machines.</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="code-panel">
        <div class="panel-bar">
          <span class="dots"><i></i><i></i><i></i></span>
          <span>$ jig prompt list &nbsp;·&nbsp; resolved across user · repo · packs</span>
          <span>JIG_PROMPT_HOME</span>
        </div>
        <div class="audit">
          <div class="receipt ok"><span class="ts">user:</span><span class="ev"><span class="k">comprehensive-review-loop</span> · <span class="d">v3 · tags=[review, loop] · 2.1 KiB</span></span></div>
          <div class="receipt ok"><span class="ts">user:</span><span class="ev"><span class="k">commit-message-rewrite</span> · <span class="d">v1 · tags=[git] · 612 B</span></span></div>
          <div class="receipt ok"><span class="ts">repo:</span><span class="ev"><span class="k">release-checklist</span> · <span class="d">v4 · tags=[release, gate] · 3.4 KiB · template: base, version</span></span></div>
          <div class="receipt ok"><span class="ts">repo:</span><span class="ev"><span class="k">pr-review-this-repo</span> · <span class="d">v2 · tags=[review] · 1.8 KiB</span></span></div>
          <div class="receipt pend"><span class="ts">pack:</span><span class="ev"><span class="k">jig-skills:bug-bisect</span> · <span class="d">v7 · read-only · vendored</span></span></div>
          <div class="receipt pend"><span class="ts">pack:</span><span class="ev"><span class="k">jig-skills:design-doc-skeleton</span> · <span class="d">v7 · read-only · vendored</span></span></div>
          <div class="receipt fail" style="margin-bottom:0;"><span class="ts">!</span><span class="ev"><span class="k">name collision</span> · <span class="x">review-loop</span> matches <span class="d">user:review-loop</span> and <span class="d">pack:jig-skills:review-loop</span> — qualify it</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- command rail -->
    <div class="cmdrail">
      <div class="cmdrail-h">commands · <span class="d">unqualified writes default to <span class="mono">user:</span> · unqualified reads must resolve to exactly one prompt</span></div>
      <div class="cmdrail-grid">
        <div><span class="d">$</span> jig <span class="hot">prompt</span> list</div>
        <div><span class="d">$</span> jig <span class="hot">prompt</span> search review --body</div>
        <div><span class="d">$</span> jig <span class="hot">prompt</span> add commit-message-rewrite --file body.md --tag git</div>
        <div><span class="d">$</span> jig <span class="hot">prompt</span> edit repo:release-checklist</div>
        <div><span class="d">$</span> jig <span class="hot">prompt</span> remove user:stale-prompt</div>
        <div><span class="d">$</span> jig <span class="hot">prompt</span> copy comprehensive-review-loop</div>
        <div class="cmdrail-wide"><span class="d">$</span> jig <span class="hot">prompt</span> get repo:release-checklist --var base=main --var version=0.4.0</div>
        <div class="cmdrail-wide"><span class="d">$</span> jig <span class="hot">prompt</span> export --output prompts.json &nbsp;&nbsp; jig <span class="hot">prompt</span> import prompts.json</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cmdrail-foot">
        <span>state · <span class="mono">~/.config/jig/prompts</span> + <span class="mono">prompt-packs/</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp; override with <span class="mono">JIG_PROMPT_HOME</span></span>
        <span class="d">runtime-owned · <span class="mono">repo:</span> prompts live in <span class="mono">.jig/prompts/</span> and are check-in safe</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
